name: anchored
desc: indicates whether the copy text shows the exact place of reference for the note.

name: targetEnd
desc: points to the end of the span to which the note is attached, if the note is not embedded in the text at that point.

name: who
desc: indicates the person, or group of people, to whom the element content is ascribed.

name: break
desc: indicates whether or not the element bearing this attribute should be considered to mark the end of an orthographic token in the same way as whitespace.

name: key
desc: the identifier used for this datatype specification

name: ref
desc: a pointer to a datatype defined in some datatype library

name: unit
desc: provides a name for the kind of unit delimited by this punctuation mark.

name: from
desc: gives the identifier of the node which is adjacent from this arc.

name: to
desc: gives the identifier of the node which is adjacent to this arc.

name: generatedBy
desc: categorizes how the content of an element was generated in a CMC environment.

name: when-custom
desc: supplies the value of a date or time in some custom standard form.

name: notBefore-custom
desc: specifies the earliest possible date for the event in some custom standard form.

name: notAfter-custom
desc: specifies the latest possible date for the event in some custom standard form.

name: from-custom
desc: indicates the starting point of the period in some custom standard form.

name: to-custom
desc: indicates the ending point of the period in some custom standard form.

name: datingPoint
desc: supplies a pointer to some location defining a named point in time with reference to which the datable item is understood to have occurred.

name: when
desc: supplies the value of the date or time in a standard form, e.g. yyyy-mm-dd.

name: notBefore
desc: specifies the earliest possible date for the event in standard form, e.g. yyyy-mm-dd.

name: notAfter
desc: specifies the latest possible date for the event in standard form, e.g. yyyy-mm-dd.

name: default
desc: indicates whether or not this element is selected by default when its parent is selected.

name: status
desc: indicates the degree of correction applied to the text.

name: dur
desc: indicates the length of this element in time.

name: evidence
desc: indicates support for the listed personal pronouns.

name: ed
desc: supplies a sigil or other arbitrary identifier for the source edition in which the associated feature (for example, a page, column, or line beginning) occurs at this point in the text.

name: edRef
desc: provides a pointer to the source edition in which the associated feature (for example, a page, column, or line beginning) occurs at this point in the text.

name: part
desc: specifies whether or not its parent element is fragmented in some way, typically by some other overlapping structure: for example a speech which is divided between two or more verse stanzas, a paragraph which is split across a page division, a verse line which is divided between two speakers.

name: style
desc: contains an expression in some formal style definition language which defines the rendering or presentation used for this element in the source text.

name: rendition
desc: points to a description of the rendering or presentation used for this element in the source text.

name: resp
desc: (responsible party) indicates the individual responsible for identifying and measuring the space.

name: source
desc: specifies the source from which some aspect of this element is drawn.

name: indentLevel
desc: specifies the level of indentation of an item using a numeric value.

name: type
desc: specifies the extensibility of the list of values specified.

name: subtype
desc: provides a sub-categorization of the element, if needed.

name: inst
desc: points to instances of the analysis or interpretation represented by the current element.

name: quantity
desc: specifies the length in the units specified

name: commodity
desc: indicates the substance that is being measured

name: notation
desc: names the notation used for the content of the element.

name: place
desc: specifies where this item is placed.

name: targetLang
desc: specifies which language to use when creating the objects in a schema if names for elements or attributes are available in more than one language.

name: target
desc: points at the specification group which logically belongs here.

name: evaluate
desc: specifies the intended meaning when the target of a pointer is itself a pointer.

name: atLeast
desc: gives a minimum estimated value for the approximate measurement.

name: atMost
desc: gives a maximum estimated value for the approximate measurement.

name: min
desc: supplies the minumum number of times the element must occur in elements which use this model class in their content model

name: max
desc: supplies the maximum number of times the element can occur in elements which use this model class in their content model

name: url
desc: refers to a non-TEI module of RELAX NG code by external location

name: sortKey
desc: supplies the sort key for this element in an index, list or group which contains it.

name: spanTo
desc: indicates the end of a span initiated by the element bearing this attribute.

name: scheme
desc: supplies the name of the language in which the constraints are defined

name: role
desc: specifies the role of this group of participants in the interaction.

name: rows
desc: indicates the number of rows in the table.

name: cols
desc: indicates the number of columns in each row of the table.

name: toWhom
desc: indicates the person, or group of people, to whom a speech act or action is directed.

name: extent
desc: indicates whether the pronunciation or orthography applies to all or part of a word.

name: sample
desc: indicates whether this division is a sample of the original source and if so, from which part.

name: n
desc: gives a number (or other label) for an element, which is not necessarily unique within the document.

name: xml:base
desc: provides a base URI reference with which applications can resolve relative URI references into absolute URI references.

name: xml:space
desc: signals an intention about how white space should be managed by applications.

name: scribe
desc: gives a name or other identifier for the scribe believed to be responsible for this hand.

name: width
desc: Where the media are displayed, indicates the display width.

name: height
desc: Where the media are displayed, indicates the display height.

name: scale
desc: Where the media are displayed, indicates a scale factor to be applied when generating the desired display size.

name: domains
desc: optionally specifies the identifiers of the elements within which all elements indicated by the contents of this element lie.

name: function
desc: describes the function (for example status, insertion, deletion, transposition) of the metamark.

name: cause
desc: classifies the cause for the variant reading, according to any appropriate typology of possible origins.

name: seq
desc: assigns a sequence number related to the order in which the encoded features carrying this attribute are believed to have occurred.

name: agent
desc: Where the difficulty in transcription arises from damage, categorizes the cause of the damage, if it can be identified.

name: group
desc: assigns an arbitrary number to each stretch of damage regarded as forming part of the same physical phenomenon.

name: start
desc: specifies entry points to the schema, i.e. which patterns may be used as the root of documents conforming to it.

name: end
desc: indicates the location within a temporal alignment at which this element ends.

name: method
desc: indicates which method is used to encode the apparatus of variants.

name: marks
desc: indicates whether or not punctation marks have been retained as content within the text.

name: eol
desc: indicates whether or not end-of-line hyphenation has been retained in a text.

name: placement
desc: indicates the positioning of punctuation marks that are associated with marked up text as being encoded within the element surrounding the text or immediately before or after it.

name: occurs
desc: specifies the number of occurrences of this element within the text.

name: name
desc: the name of the facet.

name: delim
desc: supplies a delimiting string following the reference component.

name: property
desc: A URI indicating a property definition.

name: matchPattern
desc: specifies a regular expression against which the values of other attributes can be matched.

name: ident
desc: supplies the identifier by which this element may be referenced.

name: length
desc: specifies the fixed length of the reference component.

name: datum
desc: supplies a commonly used code name for the datum employed.

name: where
desc: specifies the direction of a stage movement.

name: version
desc: supplies a version number for the encoding conventions used, if any.

name: usage
desc: specifies the optionality of the attribute.

name: time
desc: specifies how the phrase is distinct diachronically.

name: space
desc: specifies how the phrase is distinct diatopically.

name: social
desc: specifies how the phrase is distinct diastratically.

name: aloud
desc: may be used to indicate whether the quoted matter is regarded as having been vocalized or signed.

name: direct
desc: may be used to indicate whether the quoted matter is regarded as direct or indirect speech.

name: value
desc: the facet value.

name: level
desc: a code indicating the person's level of knowledge for this language.

name: pattern
desc: specifies a regular expression defining any value that is legal for this notation.

name: met
desc: contains a user-specified encoding for the conventional metrical structure of the element.

name: real
desc: contains a user-specified encoding for the actual realization of the conventional metrical structure applicable to the element.

name: rhyme
desc: specifies the rhyme scheme applicable to a group of verse lines.

name: enjamb
desc: indicates that the end of a verse line is marked by enjambement.

name: label
desc: provides a label (usually a single letter) to identify which part of a rhyme scheme this rhyming string instantiates.

name: gender
desc: specifies the gender of the participant group.

name: sex
desc: specifies the sex of the participant group.

name: discrete
desc: indicates whether the sound overlaps the surrounding speeches or interrupts them.

name: trans
desc: indicates the nature of the transition between this utterance and the previous one.

name: iterated
desc: indicates whether or not the phenomenon is repeated.

name: gradual
desc: indicates whether the writing is revealed all at once or gradually.

name: feature
desc: a paralinguistic feature.

name: modality
desc: written or spoken mode.

name: replyTo
desc: indicates to which previous post the current post replies or refers.

name: expand
desc: indicates how references to this class within a content model should be interpreted.

name: split
desc: gives the list of split values for a merged form.

name: location
desc: indicates whether the apparatus appears within the running text or external to it.

name: mergedIn
desc: gives a reference to another element, where the original appears as a merged form.

name: opt
desc: indicates whether the element is optional or not.

name: mainLang
desc: supplies a code which identifies the chief language used in the bibliographic work.

name: otherLangs
desc: one or more codes identifying any other languages used in the bibliographic work.

name: defective
desc: indicates whether the passage being quoted is defective, i.e. incomplete through loss or damage.

name: class
desc: the name of the attribute class

name: form
desc: a short project-specific name identifying the physical form of the carrier, for example as a codex, roll, fragment, partial leaf, cutting etc.

name: material
desc: a short project-defined name for the material composing the majority of the support.

name: columns
desc: specifies the number of columns per page.

name: streams
desc: indicates the number of streams per page, each of which contains an independent textual stream.

name: ruledLines
desc: specifies the number of ruled lines per column.

name: writtenLines
desc: specifies the number of written lines per column.

name: hands
desc: specifies the number of distinct hands identified within the manuscript.

name: contemporary
desc: specifies whether or not the seal is contemporary with the item to which it is affixed

name: facs
desc: points to one or more images, portions of an image, or surfaces which correspond to the current element.

name: attachment
desc: describes the method by which this surface is or was connected to the main surface.

name: flipping
desc: indicates whether the surface is attached and folded in such a way as to provide two writing surfaces.

name: ulx
desc: gives the x coordinate value for the upper left corner of a rectangular space.

name: uly
desc: gives the y coordinate value for the upper left corner of a rectangular space.

name: lrx
desc: gives the x coordinate value for the lower right corner of a rectangular space.

name: lry
desc: gives the y coordinate value for the lower right corner of a rectangular space.

name: points
desc: identifies a line within the container or bounding box specified by the parent element by means of a series of two or more pairs of numbers, each of which gives the x,y coordinates of a point on the line.

name: dim
desc: indicates whether the space is horizontal or vertical.

name: loc
desc: indicates the location of the variation, when the location-referenced method of apparatus markup is used.

name: wit
desc: contains a space-delimited list of one or more pointers indicating the witnesses which attest to a given reading.

name: varSeq
desc: provides a number indicating the position of this reading in a sequence, when there is reason to presume a sequence to the variants.

name: require
desc: supplies a list of namespaces to one of which the permitted elements must belong.

name: tags
desc: supplies one or more valid language tags for the languages specified.

name: tag
desc: supplies a valid language tag for the language concerned.

name: age
desc: specifies the age group of the participants.

name: size
desc: states the size of the graph, i.e., the number of its arcs.

name: mutual
desc: supplies a list of participants amongst all of whom the relationship holds equally.

name: parts
desc: points to constituent nyms.

name: full
desc: indicates whether the name component is given in full, as an abbreviation or simply as an initial.

name: sort
desc: specifies the sort order of the name component in relation to others within the name.

name: when-iso
desc: supplies the value of a date or time in a standard form.

name: notBefore-iso
desc: specifies the earliest possible date for the event in standard form, e.g. yyyy-mm-dd.

name: notAfter-iso
desc: specifies the latest possible date for the event in standard form, e.g. yyyy-mm-dd.

name: from-iso
desc: indicates the starting point of the period in standard form.

name: to-iso
desc: indicates the ending point of the period in standard form.

name: calendar
desc: indicates one or more systems or calendars to which the date represented by the content of this element belongs.

name: dur-iso
desc: indicates the length of this element in time.

name: mode
desc: specifies the effect of this declaration on its parent object.

name: absolute
desc: supplies an absolute value for the time.

name: interval
desc: specifies a time interval either as a positive integral value or using one of a set of predefined codes.

name: origin
desc: designates the origin of the timeline, i.e. the time at which it begins.

name: corresp
desc: points to elements that correspond to the current element in some way.

name: synch
desc: points to elements that are synchronous with the current element.

name: sameAs
desc: points to an element that is the same as the current element.

name: copyOf
desc: points to an element of which the current element is a copy.

name: next
desc: points to the next element of a virtual aggregate of which the current element is part.

name: prev
desc: points to the previous element of a virtual aggregate of which the current element is part.

name: exclude
desc: points to elements that are in exclusive alternation with the current element.

name: select
desc: selects one or more alternants; if one alternant is selected, the ambiguity or uncertainty is marked as resolved. If more than one alternant is selected, the degree of ambiguity or uncertainty is marked as reduced by the number of alternants not selected.

name: baseForm
desc: supplies the morpheme's base form.

name: force
desc: indicates the extent to which this punctuation mark conventionally separates words or phrases.

name: pre
desc: indicates whether this punctuation mark precedes or follows the unit it delimits.

name: norm
desc: provides the normalized/standardized form of information present in the source text in a non-normalized form.

name: orig
desc: gives the original string or is the empty string when the element does not appear in the source text.

name: lemma
desc: provides a lemma (base form) for the word, typically uninflected and serving both as an identifier (e.g. in dictionary contexts, as a headword), and as a basis for potential inflections.

name: lemmaRef
desc: provides a pointer to a definition of the lemma for the word, for example in an online lexicon.

name: pos
desc: (part of speech) indicates the part of speech assigned to a token (i.e. information on whether it is a noun, adjective, or verb), usually according to some official reference vocabulary (e.g. for German: STTS, for English: CLAWS, for Polish: NKJP, etc.).

name: join
desc: when present, provides information on whether the token in question is adjacent to another, and if so, on which side.

name: optional
desc: indicates whether or not the value of this feature may be present.

name: feats
desc: references the feature-value specifications making up this feature structure.

name: fVal
desc: references any element which can be used to represent the value of a feature.

name: trunc
desc: specifies whether the value represented should be truncated to give an integer value.

name: order
desc: gives the order of the tree, i.e., the number of its nodes.

name: adjTo
desc: gives the identifiers of the nodes which are adjacent to the current node.

name: adjFrom
desc: gives the identifiers of the nodes which are adjacent from the current node.

name: adj
desc: gives the identifiers of the nodes which are both adjacent to and adjacent from the current node.

name: inDegree
desc: gives the in degree of the node, the number of nodes which are adjacent from the given node.

name: outDegree
desc: gives the out degree of an intermediate node, the number of its children.

name: arity
desc: gives the maximum number of children of the root and internal nodes of the tree.

name: ord
desc: indicates whether or not the internal node is ordered.

name: children
desc: provides a list of identifiers of the elements which are the children of the intermediate node.

name: parent
desc: provides the identifier of parent of a leaf.

name: follow
desc: provides an identifier of an element which this leaf follows.

name: stdDeviation
desc: supplies a standard deviation associated with the value in question.

name: locus
desc: indicates the specific aspect of the encoding (markup or content) for which responsibility is being assigned.

name: given
desc: indicates one or more element(s) characterizing the conditions which are assumed in the assignment of a degree of confidence.

name: lang
desc: a name identifying the formal language in which the code is expressed.

name: valid
desc: indicates the intended validity of the example with respect to a schema.

name: atts
desc: supplies attribute names for which descriptions should additionally be obtained.

name: include
desc: supplies a list of the elements which are to be copied from the specified module into the schema being defined.

name: except
desc: supplies a list of namespaces or prefixed element names which are not permitted.

name: prefix
desc: specifies a default prefix which will be prepended to all patterns relating to the element, unless otherwise stated.

name: docLang
desc: specifies which languages to use when creating documentation if the description for an element, attribute, class or macro is available in more than one language.

name: defaultExceptions
desc: provides a list of namespaces and/or prefixed element names to be excluded by default from anyName in RELAX NG schemas.

name: generate
desc: indicates which alternation and sequence instantiations of a model class may be referenced. By default, all variations are permitted.

name: versionDate
desc: specifies the date on which the source text was extracted and sent to the translator

name: uri
desc: references the underlying concept of which the parent is a representation by means of some external identifier.

name: filter
desc: references an external script which contains a method to transform instances of this element to canonical TEI.

name: useSourceRendition
desc: whether to obey any rendition attribute which is present.

name: output
desc: the intended output method.

name: cssClass
desc: the name of a CSS class which should be associated with this element

name: predicate
desc: the condition under which the element bearing this attribute applies, given as an XPath predicate expression.

name: autoPrefix
desc: controls whether or not pattern names generated in the corresponding RELAX NG schema source are automatically prefixed to avoid potential nameclashes.

name: minOccurs
desc: indicates the minimum number of times this datatype may occur in an instance of the attribute being defined.

name: maxOccurs
desc: indicates the maximum number of times this datatype may occur in an instance of the attribute being defined.

name: preserveOrder
desc: if false, indicates that component elements of a sequence may occur in any order.

name: restriction
desc: supplies a string representing a regular expression providing additional constraints on the strings used to represent values of this datatype

name: module
desc: supplies a name for the module in which this object is to be declared.

name: ns
desc: specifies the namespace to which the element(s) being specified belongs.

name: att.breaking
desc: provides attributes to indicate whether or not the element concerned is considered to mark the end of an orthographic token in the same way as whitespace.

name: att.canonical
desc: provides attributes that can be used to associate a representation such as a name or title with canonical information about the object being named or referenced.

name: att.citing
desc: provides attributes for specifying the specific part of a bibliographic item being cited.

name: att.datable.custom
desc: provides attributes for normalization of elements that contain datable events to a custom dating system (i.e. other than the Gregorian used by W3 and ISO).

name: att.declaring
desc: provides attributes for elements which may be independently associated with a particular declarable element within the header, thus overriding the inherited default for that element.

name: att.docStatus
desc: provides attributes for use on metadata elements describing the status of a document.

name: att.duration.w3c
desc: provides attributes for recording normalized temporal durations.

name: att.editLike
desc: provides attributes describing the nature of an encoded scholarly intervention or interpretation of any kind.

name: att.edition
desc: provides attributes identifying the source edition from which some encoded feature derives.

name: att.indentation
desc: provides attributes for describing the indentation of a textual element on the source page or object.

name: att.internetMedia
desc: provides attributes for specifying the type of a computer resource using a standard taxonomy.

name: att.milestoneUnit
desc: provides attributes to indicate the type of section which is changing at a specific milestone.

name: att.notated
desc: provides attributes to indicate any specialised notation used for element content.

name: att.placement
desc: provides attributes for describing where on the source page or object a textual element appears.

name: att.pointing
desc: provides a set of attributes used by all elements which point to other elements by means of one or more URI references.

name: att.ranging
desc: provides attributes for describing numerical ranges.

name: att.resourced
desc: provides attributes by which a resource (such as an externally held media file) may be located.

name: att.scoping
desc: provides attributes for selecting particular elements within a document.

name: att.sortable
desc: provides attributes for elements in lists or groups that are sortable, but whose sorting key cannot be derived mechanically from the element content.

name: att.spanning
desc: provides attributes for elements which delimit a span of text by pointing mechanisms rather than by enclosing it.

name: att.styleDef
desc: provides attributes to specify the name of a formal definition language used to provide formatting or rendition information.

name: att.typed
desc: provides attributes that can be used to classify or subclassify elements in any way.

name: att.ascribed.directed
desc: provides attributes for elements representing speech or action that can be directed at a group or individual.

name: att.datable
desc: provides attributes for normalization of elements that contain dates, times, or datable events.

name: att.dimensions
desc: provides attributes for describing the size of physical objects.

name: att.divLike
desc: provides attributes common to all elements which behave in the same way as divisions.

name: att.global
desc: provides attributes common to all elements in the TEI encoding scheme.

name: att.handFeatures
desc: provides attributes describing aspects of the hand in which a manuscript is written.

name: att.media
desc: provides attributes for specifying display and related properties of external media.

name: att.naming
desc: provides attributes common to elements which refer to named persons, places, organizations etc.

name: att.pointing.group
desc: provides a set of attributes common to all elements which enclose groups of pointer elements.

name: att.segLike
desc: provides attributes for elements used for arbitrary segmentation.

name: att.damaged
desc: provides attributes describing the nature of any physical damage affecting a reading.

name: att.timed
desc: provides attributes common to those elements which have a duration in time, expressed either absolutely or by reference to an alignment map.

name: att.citeStructurePart
desc: provides attributes for selecting particular elements within a document.

name: att.formula
desc: provides attributes for defining a mathematical formula.

name: att.locatable
desc: provides attributes for referencing locations by pointing to entries in a canonical list of places.

name: att.gaijiProp
desc: provides attributes for defining the properties of non-standard characters or glyphs.

name: att.metrical
desc: defines a set of attributes that certain elements may use to represent metrical information.

name: att.enjamb
desc: provides attributes that may be used to indicate enjambement of the parent element.

name: att.entryLike
desc: provides attributes used to distinguish different styles of dictionary entries.

name: att.lexicographic
desc: provides a set of attributes for specifying standard and normalized values, grammatical functions, alternate or equivalent forms, and information about composite parts.

name: att.msExcerpt
desc: provides attributes used to describe excerpts from a manuscript placed in a description thereof.

name: att.msClass
desc: provides attributes to indicate text type or classification.

name: att.global.facs
desc: provides attributes used to express correspondence between an element and all or part of a facsimile image or surface.

name: att.global.change
desc: provides attributes allowing its member elements to specify one or more states or revision campaigns with which they are associated.

name: att.coordinated
desc: provides attributes that can be used to position their parent element within a two dimensional coordinate system.

name: att.rdgPart
desc: provides attributes to mark the beginning or ending of a fragmentary manuscript or other witness.

name: att.witnessed
desc: provides attributes used to identify the witnesses supporting a particular reading in a critical apparatus.

name: att.textCritical
desc: defines a set of attributes common to all elements representing variant readings in text critical work.

gloss: attributes for components of names usually, but not necessarily, personal names
name: att.personal
desc: common attributes for those elements which form part of a name usually, but not necessarily, a personal name.

name: att.calendarSystem
desc: provides attributes for indicating calendar systems to which a date belongs.

name: att.duration.iso
desc: provides attributes for recording normalized temporal durations.

name: att.lexicographic.normalized
desc: provides attributes for usage within word-level elements in the analysis module and within lexicographic microstructure in the dictionaries module.

name: att.global.analytic
desc: provides additional global attributes for associating specific analyses or interpretations with appropriate portions of a text.

name: att.translatable
desc: provides attributes used to indicate the status of a translatable portion of an ODD document.

name: att.predicate
desc: provides attributes for filtering by an XPath predicate expression.

name: att.combinable
desc: provides attributes indicating how multiple references to the same object in a schema should be combined.

name: att.namespaceable
desc: provides attributes indicating the target namespace for an object being created.

name: note
desc: ['contains a note or annotation.']

name: att.anchoring
desc: provides attributes for use on annotations, e.g. notes and groups of notes describing the existence and position of an anchor for annotations.

name: noteGrp
desc: ['contains a group of notes.']

name: incident
desc: ['marks any phenomenon or occurrence','not necessarily vocalized or communicative','for example incidental noises or other events affecting communication.']

name: shift
desc: ['marks the point at which some paralinguistic feature of a series of utterances by any one speaker changes.']

name: annotationBlock
desc: ['groups together various annotations','e.g. for parallel interpretations of a spoken segment.']

name: post
desc: ['a written (or spoken) contribution to a CMC interaction which has been composed (or recorded) by its author in its entirety before being transmitted over a network (e.g.','the internet) and made available on the monitor or screen of the other parties en bloc.']

name: setting
desc: ['describes one particular setting in which a language interaction takes place.']

name: milestone
desc: ['marks a boundary point separating any kind of section of a text','typically but not necessarily indicating a point at which some part of a standard reference system changes','where the change is not represented by a structural element.']

name: lb
desc: ['marks the beginning of a topographic line in some edition or version of a text.']

name: cb
desc: ['marks the beginning of a new column of a text on a multi-column page.']

name: gloss
desc: ['identifies a phrase or word used to provide a gloss or definition for some other word or phrase.']

name: term
desc: ['contains a single-word','multi-word','or symbolic designation which is regarded as a technical term.']

name: ptr
desc: ['defines a pointer to another location.']

name: ref
desc: ['defines a reference to another location','possibly modified by additional text or comment.']

name: sponsor
desc: ['specifies the name of a sponsoring organization or institution.']

name: funder
desc: ['specifies the name of an individual','institution','or organization responsible for the funding of a project or text.']

name: principal
desc: ['supplies the name of the principal researcher responsible for the creation of an electronic text.']

name: distributor
desc: ['supplies the name of a person or other agency responsible for the distribution of a text.']

name: authority
desc: ['supplies the name of a person or other agency responsible for making a work available','other than a publisher or distributor.']

name: biblFull
desc: ['contains a fully-structured bibliographic citation','in which all components of the TEI file description are present.']

name: unitDecl
desc: ['provides information about units of measurement that are not members of the International System of Units.']

name: unitDef
desc: ['contains descriptive information related to a specific unit of measurement.']

name: time
desc: ['contains a phrase defining a time of day in any format.']

name: respStmt
desc: ['supplies a statement of responsibility for the intellectual content of a text','edition','recording','or series','where the specialized elements for authors','editors','etc. do not suffice or do not apply. May also be used to encode information about individuals or organizations which have played a role in the production or distribution of a bibliographic work.']

name: resp
desc: ['contains a phrase describing the nature of a person's intellectual responsibility','or an organization's role in the production or distribution of a work.']

name: title
desc: ['contains a title for any kind of work.']

name: meeting
desc: ['contains the formalized descriptive title for a meeting or conference','for use in a bibliographic description for an item derived from such a meeting','or as a heading or preamble to publications emanating from it.']

name: publisher

name: purpose

name: graph

name: node

gloss: ['leaf or terminal node of an embedding tree']
name: eLeaf
forest

name: listForest
desc: ['provides for lists of forests.']

name: tag

name: moduleSpec

name: classSpec

name: listRef

name: exemplum

name: constraintSpec

name: conversion

name: creation
desc: ['contains information about the creation of a text.']

name: author
desc: ['in a bibliographic reference','contains the name(s) of an author','personal or corporate','of a work; for example in the same form as that provided by a recognized bibliographic name authority.']

name: editor
desc: ['contains a secondary statement of responsibility for a bibliographic item','for example the name of an individual','institution or organization','(or of several such) acting as editor','compiler','translator','etc.']

name: binding
desc: ['contains a description of one binding','i.e. type of covering','boards','etc. applied to a manuscript or other object.']

name: acquisition

name: ellipsis

name: height

name: width
desc: ['contains a measurement of an object along the axis parallel to its bottom','e.g. perpendicular to the spine of a book or codex.']

name: subst

name: att.duration
desc: provides attributes for normalization of elements that contain datable events.

name: teiHeader

name: fileDesc

name: titleStmt
desc: ['groups information about the title of a work and those responsible for its content.']

name: editionStmt
desc: ['groups information relating to one edition of a text.']

name: edition
desc: ['describes the particularities of one edition of a text.']

name: extent
desc: ['describes the approximate size of a text stored on some carrier medium or of some other object','digital or non-digital','specified in any convenient units.']

name: publicationStmt
desc: ['groups information concerning the publication or distribution of an electronic or other text.']

name: notesStmt

name: encodingDesc

name: tagsDecl
desc: ['provides detailed information about the tagging applied to a document.']

name: namespace

name: citeStructure

name: citeData
desc: ['specifies how information may be extracted from citation structures.']

name: cRefPattern

name: classDecl

name: appInfo

name: profileDesc

name: handNote

name: abstract

name: keywords

name: classCode

name: calendarDesc

name: correspContext

name: street

name: postCode

name: postBox

name: headLabel

name: headItem

name: analytic

name: series

name: pubPlace

name: imprimatur

name: docEdition

name: docImprint

name: localProp

name: unihanProp

name: unicodeProp

name: caesura

name: set

name: epilogue

name: performance

name: castList

name: role

name: view

name: transcriptionDesc

name: sense

name: gen

name: number

name: case

name: per

name: tns

name: mood

name: pos

name: subc
desc: ['contains subcategorization information (transitive/intransitive','countable/non-countable','etc.)']

name: def
desc: ['contains definition text in a dictionary entry.']

name: lang
desc: ['contains the name of a language mentioned in etymological or other linguistic discussion.']

name: catchwords

name: heraldry

name: watermark

name: msIdentifier

name: institution

name: repository

name: msContents

name: msItem

name: msItemStruct

name: objectDesc

name: supportDesc

name: support

name: collation

name: foliation

name: condition

name: layoutDesc

name: layout

name: handDesc

name: typeDesc

name: typeNote

name: scriptDesc
desc: ['contains a description of the scripts used in a manuscript or other object.']

name: scriptNote

name: musicNotation

name: additions

name: source

name: witEnd

name: objectIdentifier

name: figDesc

name: fDescr

name: arc

name: tree

name: root

name: iNode

gloss: ['underspecified embedding tree','so called because of its characteristic shape when drawn']
name: triangle
att

name: code
desc: ['contains literal code']

name: eg
desc: ['contains any kind of illustrative example.']

name: gi
desc: ['contains the name (generic identifier) of an element.']

name: val
desc: ['contains a single attribute value.']

name: specList

name: specDesc
desc: ['indicates that a description of the specified element','class','or macro should be included at this point within a document.']

name: classRef

name: elementRef
desc: ['points to the specification for some element which is to be included in a schema.']

name: macroRef
desc: ['points to the specification for some pattern which is to be included in a schema.']

name: moduleRef
desc: ['references a module which is to be incorporated into a schema.']

name: specGrp
desc: ['contains any convenient grouping of specifications for use within the current module.']

name: elementSpec

name: dataSpec
desc: ['documents a datatype.']

name: macroSpec

name: remarks
desc: ['contains any commentary or discussion about the usage of an element','attribute','class','or entity not otherwise documented within the containing element.']

name: classes
desc: ['specifies all the classes of which the documented element or class is a member or subclass.']

name: memberOf

name: outputRendition

name: paramList
desc: ['list of parameter specifications.']

name: paramSpec

name: content
desc: ['contains a declaration of the intended content model for the element (or other construct) being specified.']

name: sequence
desc: ['indicates that the constructs referenced by its children form a sequence.']

name: alternate

name: constraint
desc: ['the formal rules of a constraint']

name: attDef

name: attRef

name: dataRef

name: defaultVal

name: valItem

name: textNode

name: anyElement

desc: ['indicates the presence of an empty node within a content model.']

name: model.nameLike.agent

name: model.morphLike
desc: groups elements which provide morphological information within a dictionary entry.

name: model.lexicalRefinement
desc: elements adding further precision to the lexico-grammatical information provided for a dictionary entry.

name: model.ptrLike.form
desc: groups elements used for purposes of location of particular orthographic or pronunciation forms within a dictionary entry.

name: model.resource
desc: groups separate elements which constitute the content of a digital resource, as opposed to its metadata.

name: model.rdgPart
desc: groups elements which mark the beginning or ending of a fragmentary manuscript or other witness.

name: model.objectLike
desc: groups elements which describe objects.

name: model.orgStateLike
desc: groups elements describing changeable characteristics of an organization which have a definite duration.

name: model.placeLike
desc: groups elements used to provide information about places and their relationships.

name: model.contentPart
desc: groups elements which may appear as part of the content element.

name: model.rdgLike
desc: groups elements which contain a single reading, other than the lemma, within a textual variation.

name: model.highlighted
desc: groups phrase-level elements which are typographically distinct.

name: model.pPart.edit
desc: groups phrase-level elements for simple editorial correction and transcription.

name: model.identSynonyms
desc: groups elements which provide an explanation, equivalency, or alternative name for a markup construct.

name: model.divTop
desc: ['groups elements appearing at the beginning of a text division','.']

name: model.divBottom
desc: ['groups elements appearing at the end of a text division','.']

name: model.featureVal
desc: groups elements which represent feature values in feature structures.

name: model.pPart.data
desc: groups phrase-level elements containing names, dates, numbers, measures, and similar data.

name: model.limitedPhrase
desc: groups phrase-level elements excluding those elements primarily intended for transcription of existing sources.

name: model.divLike
desc: groups elements used to represent un-numbered generic structural divisions.

name: model.div5Like
desc: groups fifth-level structural divisions.

name: model.div6Like
desc: groups sixth-level structural divisions.

name: textClass
desc: ['groups information which describes the nature or topic of a text in terms of a standard classification scheme','thesaurus','etc.']

name: correspDesc
desc: ['contains a description of the actions related to one act of correspondence.']

name: change
desc: ['documents a change or set of changes made during the production of a source document','or during the revision of an electronic file.']

name: cit
desc: ['contains a quotation from some other document','together with a bibliographic reference to its source. In a dictionary it may contain an example text with at least one occurrence of the word form','used in the sense being described','or a translation of the headword','or an example.']

name: sic
desc: ['contains text reproduced although apparently incorrect or inaccurate.']

name: reg
desc: ['contains a reading which has been regularized or normalized in some sense.']

name: orig
desc: ['contains a reading which is marked as following the original','rather than being normalized or corrected.']

name: gb
desc: ['marks the beginning of a new gathering or quire in a transcribed codex.']

name: monogr
desc: ['contains bibliographic elements describing an item (e.g. a book or journal) published as an independent item (i.e. as a separate physical object).']

name: stage
desc: ['contains any kind of stage direction within a dramatic text or fragment.']

name: text
desc: ['contains a single text of any kind','whether unitary or composite','for example a poem or drama','a collection of essays','a novel','a dictionary','or a corpus sample.']

name: div
desc: ['contains a subdivision of the front','body','or back of a text.']

name: opener
desc: ['groups together dateline','byline','salutation','and similar phrases appearing as a preliminary group at the start of a division','especially of a letter.']

name: closer
desc: ['groups together salutations','datelines','and similar phrases appearing as a final group at the end of a division','especially of a letter.']

name: charDecl
desc: ['provides information about nonstandard characters and glyphs.']

name: writing
desc: ['contains a passage of written text revealed to participants in the course of a spoken text.']

name: objectType
desc: ['contains a word or phrase describing the type of object being referred to.']

name: history
desc: ['groups elements describing the full history of a manuscript','manuscript part','or other object.']

name: msPart
desc: ['contains information about an originally distinct manuscript or part of a manuscript','which is now part of a composite manuscript.']

name: am
desc: ['contains a sequence of letters or signs present in an abbreviation which are omitted or replaced in the expanded form of the abbreviation.']

name: mod
desc: ['represents any kind of modification identified within a single document.']

name: witness
desc: ['contains either a description of a single witness referred to within the critical apparatus','or a list of witnesses which is to be referred to by a single sigil.']

name: terrain
desc: ['contains information about the physical terrain of a place.']

name: s
desc: ['contains a sentence-like division of a text.']

name: fvLib
desc: ['assembles a library of reusable feature value elements (including complete feature structures).']

name: altIdent
desc: ['supplies the recommended XML name for an element','class','attribute','etc. in some language.']

name: param
desc: ['provides a parameter for a model behaviour by supplying its name and an XPath expression identifying the location of its content.']
